popid_1245997056="<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">You are probably familiar to the expression attachment when you work with emails e.g. To link a file to an e-mail message so that they travel to their destination together.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Within Devman attachments are simply electronic documents or files of any type that are conveniently linked to a <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"return hmshowPopup(event, popid_222534125X, this);\" class=\"popuplink\">contact<\/a> or activity in Devman. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">We use the expression <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"return hmshowPopup(event, popid_1820891002, this);\" class=\"popuplink\">Dossier<\/a> to distinguish between these simple attachments and one where you record &nbsp;more descriptive information about an attachment or set of attachments.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Devman allows you to include these documents in your database, so once &quot;uploaded&quot; they are secure and the original document can be deleted from you computer.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Devman knows the type of document it is and when you want to retrieve it say to print it opens in the original format allowing you to read it copy it and\/or print.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Physical (paper documents) must be scanned and copied to a convenient location.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Once they have been attached they become part of Devman\'s data.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
