popid_1914116818="<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The granting of funds (usually money) to nonprofit organizations by foundations and corporations.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Grants are funds given to tax-exempt nonprofit organizations or local governments by foundations, corporations, governments, small business and individuals. Most grants are made to fund a specific project and require some level of reporting. The process involves an applicant (grantee) submitting a proposal to a potential funder (grantor), either on the applicant\'s own initiative or in response to a Request for Proposal (RFP) from the funder. Other grants can be given to individuals, such as victims of natural disasters or individuals who seek to open a small business.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">This type of giving may also be referred to as organized philanthropy.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
