popid_355696879="<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">A technology used to increase the performance and\/or reliability of data storage.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The system consists of two or more disk drives (standard or SSD) working in parallel.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">There are different RAID levels each for a specific situation.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Mirroring<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Data are stored twice by writing them to both the data drive (or set of data drives) and a mirror drive (or set of drives).<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">If a drive fails, the controller uses either the data drive or the mirror drive for data recovery and continues operation. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">You need at least 2 drives for this type of array.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
