popid_355784013="<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Email<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Technically we have no way of know if an email is received, only that the SMTP server (the external server that actually sends emails) accepted it for delivery.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">If it fails to be delivered, or is delayed for more than 24 hours, emails are sent to the person listed in the reply address.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">These emails are sent by the SMTP server that currently holds the email which may or may not be the one it was originally submitted to.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\"> Formats for these emails vary.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">It is important that these emails are analysed and the details in the database are updated with the correct information in order to reduce failed emails going forward.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">SMS<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Delivery reports for SMS are more accurate than email. Generally if an SMS is of status “Delivered” in DevMan it means that it has been delivered to the handset of the intended recipient.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
