popid_1301590645="<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">A set of unified design elements and colour schemes you want to apply to email messages.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">They specify fonts, bullets, background colour, horizontal lines, images, and other design elements you want to include in outgoing e-mail messages.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Just as with physical stationery, this element is often underestimated.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">A business’ stationery can be the first impression a potential client gets of a business.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Stationery plays a vital role in whether or not a prospect chooses a particular business.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The company letterhead, envelope and business card are the three items clients see most, and have a deep impact on their decision to do business with the organization<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
