popid_1379841094X="<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Indicates where transaction details (donation and commitment ) emanate and to what extent the user can change the details.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The donation and commitment transactions can be received in the following ways:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0; padding-left: 13px; margin-left: 0;\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-family: Arial,\'Lucida Sans Unicode\',\'Lucida Grande\',\'Lucida Sans\';display:inline-block;width:13px;margin-left:-13px\">&#8226;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Integrated<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0; padding-left: 13px; margin-left: 0;\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-family: Arial,\'Lucida Sans Unicode\',\'Lucida Grande\',\'Lucida Sans\';display:inline-block;width:13px;margin-left:-13px\">&#8226;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">VCS credit card<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0; padding-left: 13px; margin-left: 0;\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-family: Arial,\'Lucida Sans Unicode\',\'Lucida Grande\',\'Lucida Sans\';display:inline-block;width:13px;margin-left:-13px\">&#8226;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Donor enters the donation and commitment details through your integrated online donation page<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0; padding-left: 13px; margin-left: 0;\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-family: Arial,\'Lucida Sans Unicode\',\'Lucida Grande\',\'Lucida Sans\';display:inline-block;width:13px;margin-left:-13px\">&#8226;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">DevMan user adds the commitment and bank details directly into DevMan.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">VCS processes the transaction and details feed automatically at the set interval into DevMan. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Once processed by VCS details cannot be changed. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Payment portal<\/span><br \/>\n\r<span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Donor enters details via a payment portal (GivenGain \/ Paygate \/ Bureau). <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The user cannot enter the donation and commitment details. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The donation and commitment details are imported into DevMan.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Once processed changes can be made only via the payment portal and re-imported into DevMan.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0; padding-left: 13px; margin-left: 0;\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-family: Arial,\'Lucida Sans Unicode\',\'Lucida Grande\',\'Lucida Sans\';display:inline-block;width:13px;margin-left:-13px\">&#8226;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Non-Integrated<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0; padding-left: 13px; margin-left: 0;\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-family: Arial,\'Lucida Sans Unicode\',\'Lucida Grande\',\'Lucida Sans\';display:inline-block;width:13px;margin-left:-13px\">&#8226;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">User – manually adds commitment details and donations, These can be freely changed later.<\/span><\/p>"
popid_308259868="<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The transaction channel indicates how the transaction detail was received into DevMan. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">This is important as it will determine how the plans are managed and whether the user can edit the details of the donation or not.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The donation details can be received in the following ways:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0; padding-left: 13px; margin-left: 0;\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-family: \'Arial\';display:inline-block;width:13px;margin-left:-13px\">&#8226;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Online giving integration <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0; padding-left: 13px; margin-left: 0;\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-family: \'Arial\';display:inline-block;width:13px;margin-left:-13px\">&#8226;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">VCS credit card - the donation \/ giving plan was set up by the donor via your online donation page that is integrated with DevMan, or the user added the plan and bank details to DevMan directly. The donation is then processed by VCS and the transaction details then feed automatically into DevMan at the set interval (see Online Giving Gateway info doc). Therefore, donation transaction details cannot be changed once added. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0; padding-left: 13px; margin-left: 0;\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-family: \'Arial\';display:inline-block;width:13px;margin-left:-13px\">&#8226;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Other integration - the donation \/ giving plan was made by the donor via a payment portal (GivenGain \/ Paygate \/ Bureau). The data is imported into DevMan and therefore donation and plan details can not be changed once added. Any changes to the plan have to be made via the payment portal then imported into DevMan.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0; padding-left: 13px; margin-left: 0;\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-family: \'Arial\';display:inline-block;width:13px;margin-left:-13px\">&#8226;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Standard<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0; padding-left: 13px; margin-left: 0;\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-family: \'Arial\';display:inline-block;width:13px;margin-left:-13px\">&#8226;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Added by user – the user manually adds donations received by other means, donation details can be updated \/ changed.<\/span><\/p>"
popid_790785382X="<p class=\"p_KidzNormalIndent\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormalIndent\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Uniform resource locator (URL) is a technical, Web-related term commonly used to:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Roughly it provides a uniform syntax for identifying a resource and providing a means of locating the resource by describing its primary access mechanism (e.g., its network ‘location’).<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">So in our context it is used to define and locate the Development Manager Web program.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Here are examples of a URL:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormalIndent\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormalIndent\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\"><a href=\"http:\/\/kcsi.kidzafrica.net\/kidznet\/Codelib\/General\/Login.aspx?UserID=Tshabalalinho\" target=\"_blank\" onclick=\"return HMTrackTopiclink(this);\" class=\"weblink\">http:\/\/kcsi.kidzafrica.net\/kidznet\/Codelib\/General\/Login.aspx?UserID=Tshabalalinho<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormalIndent2\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormalIndent2\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\"><a href=\"http:\/\/kcrm.kidzafrica.net\/kidznet\/Codelib\/General\/Login.aspx?UserID=Bernardo\" target=\"_blank\" onclick=\"return HMTrackTopiclink(this);\" class=\"weblink\">http:\/\/kcrm.kidzafrica.net\/kidznet\/Codelib\/General\/Login.aspx?UserID=Bernardo<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormalIndent2\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormalIndent2\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormalIndent\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormalIndent\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormalIndent\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormalIndent\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormalIndent\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormalIndent\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormalIndent\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormalIndent\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormalIndent\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormalIndent\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_355968524="<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The term is usually well known. In the context of DevMan it denotes a person who can &quot;use&quot; or is able to access the program via a login process and perform the functions provided. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The user must be:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span style=\"width:48px;display:inline-block\">&nbsp;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">a) added to a database and given a &quot;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\">username<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&quot; and <\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\">password<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span style=\"width:48px;display:inline-block\">&nbsp;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">b) assigned a level of access to the activities they can perform. &nbsp;<\/span><br \/>\n\r<span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The DevMan Support Team will get you started by adding your initial set of users with permissions.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">A &quot;<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\">power user<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&quot; will be assigned who can maintain the list of users and permissions.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">In addition the <\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\">power user<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\"> can assist you when you have problems logging in or when you may have forgotten your password.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1217466529X="<p class=\"p_Normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">User-based access or user-based permissions secure software and its features at the individual level.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_Normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">The simplest user-based access is a log-in name and password that either grants or denies access.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_Normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">More access includes the ability to assign specific permissions to specific users.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_2024497010X="<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The casual and novice user interacts infrequently with the application and the interactions are not always a direct requirement of job role<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">DevMan is comprehensive and handles all the activities expected in either a Grantmaking or Fundraising system.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">The help caters for the needs of this user (copious screen-shots) and the experienced user (narrative guide).<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormalIndent\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormalIndent\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1867790359X="<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Wireless Application Service Providers Association<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">A voluntary self-regulatory body with a remit of representing and self-regulating mobile-based value added services providers, otherwise known as WASPs. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_984972815="<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Add your own branding that will be displayed on the <\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">RSVP page<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\"> for the event.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">To add your template, go to <\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\">Communication &gt; Communication Templates &gt; Stationery<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\"> then select <\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\">Add<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">Make sure that the template mode is set to Web.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_KidzNormal\"><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">If you need assistance with this, please contact the <\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Support Team<\/span><span class=\"f_KidzNormal\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
